{
  "stem": "521.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And then when it was burnt to the coal, they were hammering them to-- to be powdery, and this was given to people who got diarrhea.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "But it didn't have-- one of the doctors also got diarrhea, and he just died just as the rest-- some of the other people in the camp.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "Now we have been there until April, and they, at the end, they decided that we are going to be transported further when the Russians came.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And the camp was divided into three different parts.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "Now there were people who went out regularly to work, and there were the people who didn't have much trouble anymore, as my feet became all right.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And there was the third part who couldn't walk at all, and they decided that they are going to claim that they won't be able to walk, and that was an easy solution for them.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "They were put into three huts full of people, and they were covered with blankets, and they were told that the lice is going to be killed, all the varmints.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And they really prepared those three huts really well, and there was a German man coming with cyanide, and the cyanide was pumped into those three huts.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "And the people just died.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "Except one survived.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "And that man started to yell, let me out, let me out, let me out.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And he was yelling for two solid days.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "Nobody let him out.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "The German was standing in front of the hut.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "And eventually, after two months-- after two days, they let him out and shot him.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "So that was a solution for everything.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "I remember one evening, we woke up because somebody was yelling-- it was before the end.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "And he said, don't shoot me, don't shoot me.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
